author: Jenny Gross
title: U.K.’s May Set to Reveal Most Details Yet on Brexit Proposals
text:
LONDON—British Prime Minister Theresa May outlined in the greatest detail yet her proposals for Britain’s future trading relationship with the European Union on Friday, explicitly acknowledging that leaving the bloc implied costs to the U.K. economy and would hit trade.
“Life is going to be different,” she said in a long-awaited speech. “This is a negotiation—no one can have exactly what they want.”
